Package: packetwyrm
Version: @VERSION@
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Kazuki Shimizu <kazubu@homenoc.ad.jp>
Depends: @DEPENDS@
Homepage: https://github.com/kazubu/packetwyrm
Description: FPGA-based 10G network tester (daemon, CLI and Web GUI gateway)
 PacketWyrm is an FPGA-based line-rate network tester. This package installs
 the tester daemon (packetwyrmd), the command-line client (pktwyrm) and the
 Web GUI / remote-RPC gateway (packetwyrm-proxyd), along with the shared
 runtime library, systemd units, shell completions, man pages and a Grafana
 dashboard.
 .
 The daemon opens the FPGA card BAR, runs the per-card host-plane workers and
 serves a JSON-RPC control socket. The systemd unit brings the management
 plane up only; it does not generate traffic until an explicit test start.
